{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011kmDezqtP7sFTmkUkYwkKL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: \"PRD-549.2\"\n3\ttitle: \"Scaffold builtins/ package with registry and shared helpers\"\n4\tkind: task\n5\tstatus: ready\n6\tpriority: medium\n7\teffort: s\n8\tcapability: simple\n9\tparent: \"[[PRD-549-builtins-package-split]]\"\n10\tdepends_on: []\n11\tblocks:\n12\t  - \"[[PRD-549.3-move-ensure-worktree]]\"\n13\t  - \"[[PRD-549.4-move-set-status]]\"\n14\t  - \"[[PRD-549.5-move-commit]]\"\n15\t  - \"[[PRD-549.6-move-push-branch]]\"\n16\t  - \"[[PRD-549.7-move-summarize-agent-run]]\"\n17\t  - \"[[PRD-549.8-move-commit-transcript]]\"\n18\t  - \"[[PRD-549.9-move-create-pr]]\"\n19\t  - \"[[PRD-549.10-move-lint-attribution]]\"\n20\t  - \"[[PRD-549.11-move-cleanup-worktree]]\"\n21\timpacts:\n22\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py\n23\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry.py\n24\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared.py\n25\t  - src/darkfactory/builtins.py\n26\tworkflow: null\n27\ttarget_version: null\n28\tcreated: 2026-04-08\n29\tupdated: 2026-04-08\n30\ttags:\n31\t  - refactor\n32\t  - organization\n33\t---\n34\t\n35\t# Scaffold builtins/ package with registry and shared helpers\n36\t\n37\t## Summary\n38\t\n39\tConvert `src/darkfactory/builtins.py` from a single module into a Python package by creating the `src/darkfactory/builtins/` directory with `__init__.py`, `_registry.py`, and `_shared.py`. Move the `@builtin` decorator, `BUILTIN_REGISTRY` dict, `BuiltInFunc` type alias, and shared helpers into their respective new modules. `__init__.py` re-exports the public API so all existing import sites continue to work unchanged.\n40\t\n41\t**No builtins are moved in this task.** The old `builtins.py` file is replaced by the package directory, but all builtin functions remain importable from their current location via `__init__.py` re-exports. This is an empty functional change — all tests pass before and after.\n42\t\n43\t## Requirements\n44\t\n45\t1. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/` as a Python package.\n46\t2. Move `BUILTINS`, `BuiltInFunc`, and the `@builtin` decorator into `src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry.py`.\n47\t3. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry_test.py` with unit tests for the decorator (duplicate registration raises `ValueError`, successful registration adds to dict).\n48\t4. Move shared helpers (`_run`, `_scan_for_forbidden_attribution`, `_FORBIDDEN_ATTRIBUTION_PATTERNS`) into `src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared.py`.\n49\t5. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared_test.py` with unit tests for shared helpers.\n50\t6. `src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py` imports all builtin submodules (to trigger `@builtin` registration) and re-exports the public API (`BUILTINS`, `BuiltInFunc`, `builtin`, and all nine builtin functions).\n51\t7. Every existing `from darkfactory.builtins import X` and `from darkfactory import builtins` import site continues to work unchanged.\n52\t8. All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n53\t\n54\t## Technical Approach\n55\t\n56\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry.py`\n57\t\n58\t```python\n59\tfrom __future__ import annotations\n60\tfrom typing import Callable\n61\t\n62\tBuiltInFunc = Callable[..., None]\n63\t\n64\tBUILTINS: dict[str, BuiltInFunc] = {}\n65\t\n66\tdef builtin(name: str) -> Callable[[BuiltInFunc], BuiltInFunc]:\n67\t    def decorator(func: BuiltInFunc) -> BuiltInFunc:\n68\t        if name in BUILTINS:\n69\t            raise ValueError(f\"duplicate builtin registration for {name!r}\")\n70\t        BUILTINS[name] = func\n71\t        return func\n72\t    return decorator\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared.py`\n76\t\n77\tMove from the old `builtins.py`:\n78\t- `_run(ctx, cmd, *, check, capture)` — subprocess helper with dry-run support\n79\t- `_FORBIDDEN_ATTRIBUTION_PATTERNS` — tuple of compiled regexes\n80\t- `_scan_for_forbidden_attribution(text, *, source)` — raises on forbidden patterns\n81\t\n82\t### `src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py`\n83\t\n84\t```python\n85\t\"\"\"Built-in task primitives — re-export hub.\n86\t\n87\tImports every submodule so @builtin-decorated functions register on\n88\tpackage import. Re-exports the public API for backwards compatibility.\n89\t\"\"\"\n90\tfrom darkfactory.builtins._registry import BUILTINS, BuiltInFunc, builtin\n91\t\n92\t# Import submodules to trigger registration (added by later PRDs as builtins move)\n93\t# For now, the builtin functions still live in this file until migrated.\n94\t\n95\t__all__ = [\"BUILTINS\", \"BuiltInFunc\", \"builtin\", ...]\n96\t```\n97\t\n98\tInitially, `__init__.py` contains all the builtin function definitions (copied from the old `builtins.py`) so nothing breaks. Each subsequent PRD (549.3–549.11) extracts one builtin into its own submodule and removes it from `__init__.py`.\n99\t\n100\t### Migration strategy\n101\t\n102\t1. Rename `src/darkfactory/builtins.py` → delete it.\n103\t2. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/` directory.\n104\t3. Create `_registry.py`, `_shared.py`, `__init__.py`.\n105\t4. `__init__.py` initially holds all builtin implementations (moved verbatim from old file) plus imports from `_registry` and `_shared`.\n106\t5. Verify all tests pass — this is a no-op refactor at this point.\n107\t\n108\t## Acceptance Criteria\n109\t\n110\t- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/builtins/` exists as a Python package with `__init__.py`, `_registry.py`, and `_shared.py`.\n111\t- [ ] AC-2: `_registry.py` contains the `@builtin` decorator, `BUILTINS` dict, and `BuiltInFunc` type alias.\n112\t- [ ] AC-3: `_shared.py` contains `_run`, `_scan_for_forbidden_attribution`, and `_FORBIDDEN_ATTRIBUTION_PATTERNS`.\n113\t- [ ] AC-4: `_registry_test.py` has unit tests for the decorator.\n114\t- [ ] AC-5: `_shared_test.py` has unit tests for shared helpers.\n115\t- [ ] AC-6: Every existing `from darkfactory.builtins import X` import site still resolves.\n116\t- [ ] AC-7: All 283 existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n117\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5b3278a-cf88-4c3d-896b-2252b3ec6019","uuid":"789731ed-3702-4fd0-b627-256aab1cfe8b","timestamp":"2026-04-09T02:42:33.246Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/prds/PRD-549.2-scaffold-builtins-package.md","content":"---\nid: \"PRD-549.2\"\ntitle: \"Scaffold builtins/ package with registry and shared helpers\"\nkind: task\nstatus: ready\npriority: medium\neffort: s\ncapability: simple\nparent: \"[[PRD-549-builtins-package-split]]\"\ndepends_on: []\nblocks:\n  - \"[[PRD-549.3-move-ensure-worktree]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.4-move-set-status]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.5-move-commit]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.6-move-push-branch]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.7-move-summarize-agent-run]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.8-move-commit-transcript]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.9-move-create-pr]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.10-move-lint-attribution]]\"\n  - \"[[PRD-549.11-move-cleanup-worktree]]\"\nimpacts:\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared.py\n  - src/darkfactory/builtins.py\nworkflow: null\ntarget_version: null\ncreated: 2026-04-08\nupdated: 2026-04-08\ntags:\n  - refactor\n  - organization\n---\n\n# Scaffold builtins/ package with registry and shared helpers\n\n## Summary\n\nConvert `src/darkfactory/builtins.py` from a single module into a Python package by creating the `src/darkfactory/builtins/` directory with `__init__.py`, `_registry.py`, and `_shared.py`. Move the `@builtin` decorator, `BUILTIN_REGISTRY` dict, `BuiltInFunc` type alias, and shared helpers into their respective new modules. `__init__.py` re-exports the public API so all existing import sites continue to work unchanged.\n\n**No builtins are moved in this task.** The old `builtins.py` file is replaced by the package directory, but all builtin functions remain importable from their current location via `__init__.py` re-exports. This is an empty functional change — all tests pass before and after.\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/` as a Python package.\n2. Move `BUILTINS`, `BuiltInFunc`, and the `@builtin` decorator into `src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry.py`.\n3. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry_test.py` with unit tests for the decorator (duplicate registration raises `ValueError`, successful registration adds to dict).\n4. Move shared helpers (`_run`, `_scan_for_forbidden_attribution`, `_FORBIDDEN_ATTRIBUTION_PATTERNS`) into `src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared.py`.\n5. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared_test.py` with unit tests for shared helpers.\n6. `src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py` imports all builtin submodules (to trigger `@builtin` registration) and re-exports the public API (`BUILTINS`, `BuiltInFunc`, `builtin`, and all nine builtin functions).\n7. Every existing `from darkfactory.builtins import X` and `from darkfactory import builtins` import site continues to work unchanged.\n8. All existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n\n## Technical Approach\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/_registry.py`\n\n```python\nfrom __future__ import annotations\nfrom typing import Callable\n\nBuiltInFunc = Callable[..., None]\n\nBUILTINS: dict[str, BuiltInFunc] = {}\n\ndef builtin(name: str) -> Callable[[BuiltInFunc], BuiltInFunc]:\n    def decorator(func: BuiltInFunc) -> BuiltInFunc:\n        if name in BUILTINS:\n            raise ValueError(f\"duplicate builtin registration for {name!r}\")\n        BUILTINS[name] = func\n        return func\n    return decorator\n```\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/_shared.py`\n\nMove from the old `builtins.py`:\n- `_run(ctx, cmd, *, check, capture)` — subprocess helper with dry-run support\n- `_FORBIDDEN_ATTRIBUTION_PATTERNS` — tuple of compiled regexes\n- `_scan_for_forbidden_attribution(text, *, source)` — raises on forbidden patterns\n\n### `src/darkfactory/builtins/__init__.py`\n\n```python\n\"\"\"Built-in task primitives — re-export hub.\n\nImports every submodule so @builtin-decorated functions register on\npackage import. Re-exports the public API for backwards compatibility.\n\"\"\"\nfrom darkfactory.builtins._registry import BUILTINS, BuiltInFunc, builtin\n\n# Import submodules to trigger registration (added by later PRDs as builtins move)\n# For now, the builtin functions still live in this file until migrated.\n\n__all__ = [\"BUILTINS\", \"BuiltInFunc\", \"builtin\", ...]\n```\n\nInitially, `__init__.py` contains all the builtin function definitions (copied from the old `builtins.py`) so nothing breaks. Each subsequent PRD (549.3–549.11) extracts one builtin into its own submodule and removes it from `__init__.py`.\n\n### Migration strategy\n\n1. Rename `src/darkfactory/builtins.py` → delete it.\n2. Create `src/darkfactory/builtins/` directory.\n3. Create `_registry.py`, `_shared.py`, `__init__.py`.\n4. `__init__.py` initially holds all builtin implementations (moved verbatim from old file) plus imports from `_registry` and `_shared`.\n5. Verify all tests pass — this is a no-op refactor at this point.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC-1: `src/darkfactory/builtins/` exists as a Python package with `__init__.py`, `_registry.py`, and `_shared.py`.\n- [ ] AC-2: `_registry.py` contains the `@builtin` decorator, `BUILTINS` dict, and `BuiltInFunc` type alias.\n- [ ] AC-3: `_shared.py` contains `_run`, `_scan_for_forbidden_attribution`, and `_FORBIDDEN_ATTRIBUTION_PATTERNS`.\n- [ ] AC-4: `_registry_test.py` has unit tests for the decorator.\n- [ ] AC-5: `_shared_test.py` has unit tests for shared helpers.\n- [ ] AC-6: Every existing `from darkfactory.builtins import X` import site still resolves.\n- [ ] AC-7: All 283 existing tests pass. `just test`, `just lint`, `just typecheck`, `just format-check` all clean.\n","numLines":117,"startLine":1,"totalLines":117}}}
